f=AI & Agents/forge/custom/technique-adoption/SKILL.md · in=gate new method/technique (prompting pattern, retrieval approach, agent-loop design, new model) passes between "interesting" "in fleet": benchmark our tasks, migration cost, adoption rec. · p=field ships something shiny weekly. Without gate, fleet churns novelty; one, measured improvements land their true migration cost attached. · wu=edge's pilot-spec-handoff delivers emerging-tech pilot involves methods., scout's ecosystem scan lesson suggests candidate technique., agent requests technique change ("should switch Y?"). · st:/ Protocol=INTAKE (candidate claimed benefit source) CHEAP KILL (does claim even apply our task types? conflicts rails/charter? reject early, log why) BENCHMARK (benchmarking-discipline, golden set) MIGRATION COST (config changes, prompt rework, re-golden-runs, skill edits needed itemized) REC (adopt watch reject, registry Rail proposal adoption changes configs skills). · in=Claims quoted, tested never transcribed recs. "Paper says +30%" becomes "our golden set says X". cheap-kill step genuinely cheap: one-page applicability check, mini-benchmark. candidates die that's gate working. Migration cost itemized honestly, including anneal's skill-edit proposals trigger gauge's re-baselining. technique whose migration exceeds measured benefit gets `watch`, `adopt`. verdict logged registry (adopt reject watch, re-check dates watch) fleet never re-evaluates candidate scratch unknowingly. Adoption never self-executing: rec becomes Rail proposal; board/operator decide; anneal edits skills; gauge re-measures. forge ever recommends. · of=Adoption memo: candidate, source, cheap-kill result benchmark summary (variance included), itemized migration cost, verdict confidence flag, registry entry ref. · pr=Benchmarks over papers; our tasks over their demos., Rejection logged reason successful outcome., Migration cost part result, footnote. · f=Candidate can't benchmarked (needs infra lack, golden set gap)